COMMAND: Autumn Watch is active.
COMMAND: You are our eyes in the North Atlantic. SOSUS arrays are tracking a November-class submarine that entered the GIUK gap fourteen hours ago.
COMMS: Your task force is positioned to intercept. One Burke-class destroyer, one Perry-class frigate.
COMMS: Last bearing from SOSUS: zero-four-five relative to your position. Range estimated sixty to eighty nautical miles. Contact is heading southwest at eight knots.
INTEL: Assessment: this boat is running a standard transit profile. If it holds course, it crosses your patrol box within four hours.
COMMS: Find it. Fix it. Track it. Weapons free on confirmed hostile subsurface contacts.
COMMS: COMMS out.
